\r\n469\r\n00:31:01,120 --> 00:31:02,952\r\nSir, I apologize,\r\nthis woman...\r\nCongressman.\r\n\r\n470\r\n00:31:03,040 --> 00:31:04,190\r\nMiss, you need to\r\nstep away from the door.\r\n\r\n471\r\n00:31:04,280 --> 00:31:06,360\r\nIf I could just\r\nhave one second.\r\nStep away from the...\r\n\r\n472\r\n00:31:07,160 --> 00:31:08,355\r\nWho are you?\r\n\r\n473\r\n00:31:08,440 --> 00:31:11,353\r\n<i>My name is Zoe Barnes.\r\nI'm a reporter at\r\nthe Washington Herald.</i>\r\n\r\n474\r\n00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:16,833\r\nIt is after\r\n10:30 at night\r\nand this is my home.\r\n\r\n475\r\n00:31:16,920 --> 00:31:21,119\r\nI do not allow...\r\nWe're part of a mutual\r\nadmiration society.\r\n\r\n476\r\n00:31:24,480 --> 00:31:25,994\r\nYou're a fan of the symphony.\r\n\r\n477\r\n00:31:26,960 --> 00:31:29,316\r\nMore for the\r\npeople-watching\r\nthan the music.\r\n\r\n478\r\n00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:34,759\r\nIt's all right, Steve.\r\nCome on in, Ms. Barnes.\r\n\r\n479\r\n00:31:50,080 --> 00:31:51,480\r\nIt's strong.\r\n\r\n480\r\n00:31:51,560 --> 00:31:53,040\r\nYou'd prefer it weak?\r\n\r\n481\r\n00:31:53,120 --> 00:31:55,316\r\nNo, the stronger the better.\r\n\r\n482\r\n00:31:58,680 --> 00:32:00,239\r\nThere's no harm in looking.\r\n\r\n483\r\n00:32:00,320 --> 00:32:02,755\r\nThat's a cheap ploy.\r\n\r\n484\r\n00:32:02,840 --> 00:32:04,638\r\nIt's cheap but effective.\r\n\r\n485\r\n00:32:06,360 --> 00:32:08,716\r\nWell, you certainly have\r\nmy undivided attention.\r\n\r\n486\r\n00:32:08,840 --> 00:32:11,753\r\nGood,\r\nthe reason I'm here...\r\nOh...\r\n\r\n487\r\n00:32:11,840 --> 00:32:14,036\r\nIs foreplay over?\r\n\r\n488\r\n00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:17,597\r\nI read somewhere\r\nthat JFK never lasted\r\nmore than three minutes.\r\n\r\n489\r\n00:32:17,680 --> 00:32:19,239\r\nThe point being?\r\n\r\n490\r\n00:32:19,320 --> 00:32:20,515\r\nTime is precious.\r\n\r\n491\r\n00:32:20,600 --> 00:32:22,831\r\nPowerful people don't have\r\nthe luxury of foreplay.\r\n\r\n492\r\n00:32:22,960 --> 00:32:26,158\r\nOkay. So why are\r\nyou here, Ms. Barnes?\r\n\r\n493\r\n00:32:26,760 --> 00:32:28,672\r\nI need somebody I can talk to.\r\n\r\n494\r\n00:32:28,800 --> 00:32:31,872\r\nWe're talking.\r\nTell me what\r\nwe're talking about.\r\n\r\n495\r\n00:32:33,360 --> 00:32:36,000\r\nI protect your identity,\r\nI print whatever you tell me.\r\n\r\n496\r\n00:32:36,080 --> 00:32:37,878\r\nAnd I'll never\r\nask any questions.\r\n\r\n497\r\n00:32:37,960 --> 00:32:40,350\r\nAnd what makes you think\r\nI don't already have\r\nsuch an arrangement\r\n\r\n498\r\n00:32:40,440 --> 00:32:41,561\r\nwith one of your colleagues?\r\n\r\n499\r\n00:32:41,640 --> 00:32:44,040\r\nBecause if you did,\r\nyou wouldn't have\r\nlet me through the door.\r\n\r\n500\r\n00:32:45,680 --> 00:32:48,036\r\nI've led a very long,\r\nvery successful career\r\n\r\n501\r\n00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:50,635\r\navoiding this sort of\r\nintrigue with the press.\r\n\r\n502\r\n00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:52,677\r\nI can't see any\r\nadvantage in starting now.\r\n\r\n503\r\n00:32:52,760 --> 00:32:54,319\r\nBut is there any disadvantage?\r\n\r\n504\r\n00:32:54,400 --> 00:32:55,834\r\nSloppiness, for one.\r\n\r\n505\r\n00:32:55,920 --> 00:32:57,832\r\nI promise you\r\nabsolute discretion.\r\n\r\n506\r\n00:32:57,920 --> 00:33:00,799\r\nSo we're talking about trust.\r\n\r\n507\r\n00:33:00,880 --> 00:33:02,314\r\nUse whatever word you like.\r\n\r\n508\r\n00:33:02,400 --> 00:33:04,392\r\nWords matter very\r\nmuch, Ms. Barnes.\r\n\r\n509\r\n00:33:04,480 --> 00:33:06,790\r\nYou should care\r\nmore about them,\r\ngiven your profession.\r\n\r\n510\r\n00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:09,960\r\nThen yes, your trust.\r\n\r\n511\r\n00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:13,396\r\nSo which Zoe Barnes\r\nam I to trust?\r\n\r\n512\r\n00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:17,311\r\nThe one who wrote\r\nabout the fireman\r\nthat married the meter maid?\r\n\r\n513\r\n00:33:17,400 --> 00:33:19,960\r\nOr the one who\r\nauthored a very\r\nfine article\r\n\r\n514\r\n00:33:20,080 --> 00:33:22,640\r\non a new jogging path\r\nin Rock Creek Park.\r\n\r\n515\r\n00:33:22,720 --> 00:33:24,518\r\nDon't be flattered.\r\nI read everything.\r\n\r\n516\r\n00:33:24,600 --> 00:33:26,512\r\nI'm better than what\r\nthey have me doing.\r\n\r\n517\r\n00:33:29,720 --> 00:33:30,920\r\nYou know what that feels like.\r\n\r\n518\r\n00:33:31,080 --> 00:33:32,309\r\nDo I?\r\n\r\n519\r\n00:33:32,520 --> 00:33:34,671\r\nYou would have made\r\na great Secretary of State.\r\n\r\n520\r\n00:33:39,480 --> 00:33:41,756\r\nHow exactly may I\r\nhelp you, Ms. Barnes?\r\n\r\n521\r\n00:33:43,760 --> 00:33:45,877\r\nYou must know\r\nthe administration's\r\nlegislative agenda.\r\n\r\n522\r\n00:33:46,600 --> 00:33:48,319\r\nWhat's coming up first.\r\nI may.\r\n\r\n523\r\n00:33:49,520 --> 00:33:50,556\r\nWill you tell me?\r\n\r\n524\r\n00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:52,229\r\nWhat would be your guess?\r\n\r\n525\r\n00:33:55,440 --> 00:33:57,238\r\nEducation.\r\nWhy?\r\n\r\n526\r\n00:33:57,320 --> 00:34:01,109\r\nImmigration is\r\ntoo controversial.\r\nTax-reform isn't sexy enough.\r\n\r\n527\r\n00:34:02,480 --> 00:34:03,960\r\nEveryone can get\r\nbehind children.\r\n\r\n528\r\n00:34:06,520 --> 00:34:07,556\r\nIs it education?\r\n\r\n529\r\n00:34:07,640 --> 00:34:11,031\r\nYou might very\r\nwell think that.\r\nI couldn't possibly comment.\r\n\r\n530\r\n00:34:11,280 --> 00:34:12,430\r\nA hint.\r\n\r\n531\r\n00:34:12,960 --> 00:34:14,076\r\nIt's late, Ms. Barnes.\r\n\r\n532\r\n00:34:14,200 --> 00:34:15,350\r\nCan we talk again?\r\n\r\n533\r\n00:34:15,440 --> 00:34:18,319\r\nI hope you'll understand\r\nthat I want to\r\nsleep on all this.\r\n\r\n534\r\n00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:20,119\r\nI never make such big decisions\r\n\r\n535\r\n00:34:20,200 --> 00:34:22,795\r\nso long after sunset\r\nand so far from dawn.\r\n\r\n536\r\n00:34:28,640 --> 00:34:30,552\r\nMy cell phone's on the back.\r\n\r\n537\r\n00:34:31,480 --> 00:34:33,392\r\nDid you put Ms. Barnes\r\nin the visitors' ledger?\